-c- wrote:Lawn bowls, I think they're called.Yep. For North American readers, think: curling, but on grass. The weighted balls can curl on their own (so, no brooms needed) and the target area changes slightly for each end (because the target is a small ball that gets rolled down the lawn at the start, rather than a fixed target area).
